      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Pour $z \\in \\Z$, on pose $f_{a,b}(z) = az+b$.\n\n      Montrer que $\\phi : {\\Z^2} \\to {\\Z^{\\Z}},  {(a,b)} \\mapsto {f_{a,b}}$\n      est un morphisme pour $*$ et $\\circ$.",
        "html": "<p>Pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(z \\in \\Z\\)</span>, on pose <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f_{a,b}(z) = az+b\\)</span>.</p>\n<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\phi : {\\Z^2} \\to {\\Z^{\\Z}},  {(a,b)} \\mapsto {f_{a,b}}\\)</span> est un morphisme pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(*\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\circ\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
